JOHANNESBURG - Former Finance Minister Nhlanhla Nene will take the reins at the Wits Business School rfom Monday. Nene will serve as the interim director until the school can appoint a new leader in the next academic year.READ: EXCLUSIVE: Nene opens up about sackingPresident Jacob Zuma fired Nene as finance minister in December 2015.The move caused economic chaos and Zuma was forced to rehire Pravin Gordhan to the role just a few days later.Nene is a non-executive director at Allan Gray and a resident adviser at Thebe Investment Corporation.Wits says Nene s economic insight will add value to the school s courses.eNCA